qas.question: What event preceded the domination of Estonia by different European powers?
Which three nations occupied Estonia up until 1918?
What era contains the oldest records of written Estonia works?
What document dated in 1241 contains place and family names?

context: The Estonian literature refers to literature written in the Estonian language (ca. 1 million speakers). The domination of Estonia after <a0_0>the Northern Crusades<a0_0/>, from the 13th century to 1918 by <a1_0>Germany, Sweden, and Russia<a1_0/> resulted in few early written literary works in the Estonian language. The oldest records of written Estonian date from <a2_0>the 13th century<a2_0/>. Originates Livoniae in Chronicle of Henry of Livonia contains Estonian place names, words and fragments of sentences. <a3_0>The Liber Census Daniae<a3_0/> (1241) contains Estonian place and family names.
